As if to strike a quick terror into them, by this time being the first 
assailant himself, Moby Dick had turned, and was now coming for the three 
crews. Ahab’s boat was central; and cheering his men, he told them he would 
take the whale head-and-head,—that is, pull straight up to his forehead,—a 
not uncommon thing; for when within a certain limit, such a course excludes the 
